      • setOptions

        public static void setOptions(IOptionHolder holder,
              IOption<?>... options)
        Sets multiple options.

        Applies each option to holder in the specified order. The action depends on whether the option's value() is set: if non-null setOption will be invoked on the holder with the specified key and value, otherwise unsetOption will be called.

        Parameters:
        holder - is a non-null option holder.
        options - are zero or more option objects.
        Since:
        0.07
